FROM python:3.12-slim

WORKDIR /app

COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt

COPY . .

CMD ["python", "app.py"]

------------------------------

Pipeline for this:

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git 'https://github.com/example/app.git'
            }
        }
        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER} .'
            }
        }
        stage('Push Image') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker push myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy to K8s') {
            steps {
                sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
            }
        }
    }
}

-------------------------------

No Build stage — same as Node.js, pip install happens inside Docker.

All 3 compared:

+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
|                   | Java                      | Node.js                | Python               |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
| Build in pipeline | mvn clean package         | ✗                      | ✗                    |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
| Install in Docker | ✗                         | npm install            | pip install          |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
| Dependency file   | pom.xml                   | package*.json          | requirements.txt     |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
| Base image        | eclipse-temurin:21-jre    | node:20-alpine         | python:3.12-slim     |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
| Start cmd         | java -jar app.jar         | npm start              | python app.py        |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+
| Port              | 8080                      | 3000                   | 5000                 |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------+----------------------+

Why COPY requirements.txt . first?

Docker layer caching:
- Same caching reason as Node.js.
- If only source code changes, Docker skips pip install
  and reuses the cached dependency layer.
- This makes rebuilds faster.

